Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until
tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@olive oil{1%tbsp} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds.
Chop into 1cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain the
@sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Drain the @mozzarella{1} and pat it dry with #kitchen paper{}, making sure you
squeeze out as much liquid as possible. Then tear it into pieces.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Preheat the #grill{} to high.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once
the oil is hot, add the pepper and corn. Stir-fry until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Lower the heat to medium-high, then add the garlic and @harissa paste{50%g} (add
less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @creme fraiche{75%g},
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts).

Bring the sauce to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{4-5%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

Once ready, combine the cooked pasta and sauce in whichever pan is biggest. Add
a splash of water if it's a little too thick, then transfer to an appropriately
sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Scatter over the mozzarella and Cheddar.

Pop the dish under the grill and cook until the cheese is bubbling and golden,
~{7-8%minutes}.

When ready, share the harissa pasta bake between your bowls.

Top with a handful of @wild rocket{20%g} to finish.

Enjoy!